# SmoothSend Frontend Environment Variables

# ========================================
# RELAYER API CONFIGURATION
# ========================================

# URL of your SmoothSend relayer backend
# Local development:
NEXT_PUBLIC_RELAYER_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Production (uncomment when deploying):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_RELAYER_URL=https://api.smoothsend.io

# ========================================
# OPTIONAL CONFIGURATIONS
# ========================================

# Analytics (optional)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ANALYTICS_ID=

# Sentry Error Tracking (optional)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=

# ========================================
# DEVELOPMENT NOTES
# ========================================

# 1. Copy this file to .env.local:
#    cp .env.example .env.local
#
# 2. Make sure your relayer is running:
#    cd ../relayer && npm run dev
#
# 3. Start the frontend:
#    npm run dev
#
# 4. The RelayerStatusBar will automatically
#    check http://localhost:3000/api/v1/relayer/health
#
# 5. You should see a green "Relayer Online" status!

# ========================================
# PRODUCTION DEPLOYMENT
# ========================================

# When deploying to Vercel/Netlify/etc:
#
# 1. Set NEXT_PUBLIC_RELAYER_URL to your production relayer URL
# 2. Make sure CORS is configured on the relayer to allow your frontend domain
# 3. Check relayer .env has ALLOWED_ORIGINS set correctly
